Part 1 — Create a Snapshot (Backup):
      Step 1 — Navigate to Volumes:
            Go to AWS Console → EC2
            In the left panel, under Elastic Block Store → Click "Volumes"
            Select the EBS Volume you want to back up
      Step 2 — Create a Snapshot:
            Click Actions → "Create Snapshot"
            Enter a Name/Description for the snapshot
            (e.g., MyEBSBackup-Snapshot)
            Click "Create Snapshot" ✅

📦 Part 2 — Create a New Volume from Snapshot (Move to Another Instance/Region):
      Step 1 — Navigate to Snapshots:
            In the left panel, under Elastic Block Store → Click "Snapshots"
            Select your newly created snapshot
      Step 2 — Create Volume from Snapshot:
            Click Actions → "Create Volume from Snapshot"
            Configure the volume:
     --------------------------------------------------------
      Setting	              Value
      Volume Type	          gp2(or same as previous)
      Size	                Same or larger than original
      Availability Zone	    Same or different region ✅
      --------------------------------------------------------------
              Click "Create Volume"
              The new volume will now appear in the Volumes screen ✅
              💡 This is how you move an EBS volume from one EC2 instance to another — even across different regions!

🗑️ Part 3 — Set Up Recycle Bin (Retention Rule):
      Step 1 — Navigate to Recycle Bin:
            In the left panel → Click "Snapshots"
            Click "Recycle Bin"
      Step 2 — Create a Retention Rule:
            Click "Create Retention Rule"
            Configure the rule:
     ---------------------------------------------------
      Setting	            Value
      Rule Name	e.g.,     EBSSnapshotRetentionRule
      Resource Type	      EBS Snapshots
      Retention Period	    1 Day
      ----------------------------------------------------
      Click "Create Retention Rule" ✅
      💡 This means if a snapshot is deleted, it will be kept in Recycle Bin for 1 day before permanent deletion

♻️ Part 4 — Delete and Recover Snapshot:
      Step 1 — Delete the Snapshot:
              Go to Snapshots
              Select your snapshot
              Click Actions → "Delete Snapshot" → Confirm
      Step 2 — Recover from Recycle Bin:
              Go to Recycle Bin → Click "Resources"
              Select the deleted snapshot
              Click "Recover" ✅
      Step 3 — Verify Recovery:
              Go back to Snapshots screen
              The recovered snapshot will now be visible and available again ✅
